Package: DetectConf
Title: Probabilistic Confidence Surfaces for Invasive Species GBIF Records
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Eva", "Benavides Rios",
           email = "eva.benavides.rios@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A prototype R framework for interpreting detection confidence
    in GBIF invasive species occurrence records. DetectConf produces a
    reliability map of the observation system — shifting the question from
    "where can the species establish?" to "where would we have seen it if
    it were there?" The framework models the observation process rather
    than habitat suitability, treating sampling bias as informative
    structure rather than noise to be corrected. A Bayesian Additive
    Regression Trees model is fit to presence cells and pseudo-absences
    drawn from invasion-front envelopes, with predictors including
    effort intensity, taxonomic relevance, recorder dominance, temporal
    coverage, coordinate uncertainty, spatial corroboration of nearby
    records, and national-level introduction priors from the SInAS
    database (Seebens et al. 2017). Demonstrated on Asclepias syriaca
    in Belgium for the GBIF Ebbe Nielsen Challenge 2026.
